Colombia’s Chocolates to Buy Ice Cream Maker for $38.7 Million

-- B y   H e a t h e r   W a l s h
-- 
2011-02-19T17:00:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-19/colombia-s-chocolates-to-buy-ice-cream-maker-for-38-7-million.html
  Grupo Nacional de Chocolates SA ,  Colombia ’s biggest food producer, said it agreed to purchase
control of the Dominican Republic’s largest ice cream maker,
Helados Bon SA, for $38.7 million.  Chocolates will hold a 73 percent stake in Helados Bon, the
Colombian company said in a statement posted last night on the
 website  of Colombia’s securities regulator.  Helados Bon makes the Bon ice cream brand, which it
distributes through a network of 337 stores, according to the
statement.  Chocolates is the maker of Jet and Gol chocolate candies,
and Colcafe, an instant coffee. Shares fell 400 pesos, or 1.7
percent, to 23,040 pesos yesterday in Bogota trading.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Heather Walsh in Bogota at 
 hlwalsh@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  